Kuh. takes quid refert to mean ‘ What does it matter whether we are gods or to be with the gods?’ But this does not seem to suit the context adsunt enim qui naec non probent, since this must¹ refer to uirtusiurisiurandi? quid refert seems rather to mean What differeuce does it make whether it is less an evil than anything else is, or whether it is more a good than anything else is?

lt does make a difference, for we must shew that even if the animus is mortalis, death, though not a positive good, is less an evil than anything else is.
